The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, April 17, 2004 				 Board recast, PM Sinha is chairman
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENTCalcutta, April 16: The Bata board has been recast with P. M. Sinha, former chief executive officer of Pepsi Cola International South Asia, being roped in as the non-executive chairman.																								Sinha takes over charge from Constantin Salameh, who was serving as acting chairman following A. L. Mudaliars retirement. 																								Salameh, senior vice-president and chief financial officer of the Bata group, was inducted as the acting chairman of Bata India at the companys board meeting held on March 10.																								Sinha is currently on the boards of ICICI Bank, Wipro Limited, Indian Oil Corporation, Lafarge India Limited and the Azim Premji Foundation. 																								Nirmalya Kumar, the US-based professor of marketing, has also joined the Bata board.																								To provide continuity and experience of the independent directors, V. Narayanan and A. K. Thakur will continue as members of the board.																								The board meeting held today did not discuss the fist quarter results. Director finance P. K. Nag said the results would be announced later this month.
